<P>
Photo, For Safety's Sake: A new pedestrian bridge over the Metro Rail Blue Line 
at 105th Street and Grandee Avenue in Watts was dedicated Thursday. Serving as 
color guard for the ceremonies were members of the California Cadet Corps from 
nearby Markham Intermediate School. The steel walkway replaces a street-level 
pedestrian crossing and was designed in harmony with the Watts Towers. Another 
pedestrian bridge has been built over the tracks in the city of Compton and is 
scheduled to be dedicated next week. PATRICK DOWNS/ Los Angeles Times 
</P>
