<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION FOOTBALL FINALS; 
</P>
<P>
PARAMOUNT STREAK ON THE LINE AGAINST CAPISTRANO VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIC SHEPARD, TIMES PREP SPORTS EDITOR 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At first glance, Saturday night's Southern Section Division II football title 
game looks more like a mismatch than a matchup. 
</P>
<P>
Paramount (13-0) comes into the game with the section's longest winning streak 
at 21 games. 
</P>
<P>
The Pirates are also going for their third consecutive championship. 
</P>
<P>
Capistrano Valley (11-2), meanwhile, finished third in the South Coast League 
this season behind Mission Viejo and El Toro. 
</P>
<P>
But the 7:30 p.m. showdown at Santa Ana Stadium could be the best of a long 
weekend. 
</P>
<P>
Paramount lost most of its top players from last season to graduation, but 
Coach Ken Sutch overcame that, proving that he reloads rathers than rebuilds. 
</P>
<P>
Running back Leon Neal has been the key offensive player in playoff victories 
over Rio Mesa, Pasadena Muir and El Toro. 
</P>
<P>
Capistrano Valley rebounded from its slow start in league play, defeating 
Mission Viejo, 26-24, in the playoff semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
The Cougars' leaders are quarterback Tony Solliday and receiver Dave Poltl. 
</P>
<P>
A look at the rest of the Southern Section championship games: 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA120790-0062 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 318903 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
December 7, 1990, Friday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
