<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Zan Dubin and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PROCRA 
</P>
<P>
INATION: Monday is the deadline for the first of two property tax payments, but 
if you miss it, don't get upset. The county tax collector doesn't. . . . Late 
penalties -- 10% for the first payment, 10% and $20 for the second, plus 1.5% 
interest per month after July -- brings about $15 million into local government 
treasuries each year. . . . And there's no question the taxes will be paid, 
says Tax Collector Bob Citron. This year, 23,649 property owners were 
delinquent, but all except 14 paid up before their property was auctioned. Zan 
Dubin and Steve Emmons 
