<P>
FOUR PEOPLE HURT IN FREEWAY PILEUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four people were taken to local hospitals Thursday after a tractor-trailer and 
seven cars collided in a chain-reaction pileup on the Artesia Freeway, the 
California Highway Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
It was not known how the 7:25 a.m. accident at the Orangethorpe Avenue exit 
started, CHP officer Linda Burrus said. 
</P>
<P>
The four unidentified drivers were treated at two nearby hospitals and 
released, she said. 
</P>
<P>
Burrus said that accident made the morning rush hour miserable on both the 
westbound and eastbound sides of Artesia Freeway while cleanup crews removed 
the wreckage. 
</P>
<P>
About 40 feet of the center divider was damaged when the truck nearly tore 
through it, Burrus said. It was unclear if the truck caused the accident or if 
it plowed into the center divider to evade the colliding cars. 
</P>
<P>
Burrus said the investigation is continuing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
