</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Roberts Returns to Broadcasting: Kenneth J. Roberts, the former concert 
promoter who built KROQ-FM in Los Angeles into a rock radio giant before 
selling it for a then-record $45 million in 1986, has jumped back into the 
local broadcast scene with the acquisition of two small FM stations. 
</P>
<P>
Roberts said he has agreed to purchase KOCM-FM in Newport Beach and its sister 
station, KSRF-FM in Santa Monica, for $17.7 million. The two stations, both 
broadcasting at the same frequency -- 103.1 megahertz -- are owned by companies 
controlled by businessman Steven Udvar-Hazy, broadcast executive Jack Siegal 
and attorney Leonard Weinberg, all of Los Angeles. Roberts said the transfer of 
ownership should be completed by March 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
