<P>
SLAIN MAN FOUND IN DANA POINT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DANA POINT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A resident walking behind the Dana Point Community Center found the body of a 
44-year-old county worker on a basketball court in a public park, an Orange 
County Sheriff's Department spokesman said today. Authorities said he had been 
shot repeatedly. 
</P>
<P>
The body of Jimmy Lee Oxford of Perris was discovered last night on the 
darkened basketball court in a pool of blood, Sheriff's Department Lt. Bob 
Rivas said. He had been shot several times in the upper body and head. 
</P>
<P>
Homicide detectives have not determined how long the body had been there, 
whether the shooting took place there or what the motive may have been, Rivas 
said. 
</P>
<P>
"That all is still being investigated," Rivas said. 
</P>
<P>
Rivas said that an autopsy was scheduled this morning but that results will not 
be available until late this afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
Police believe that Oxford, a county Environmental Management Agency employee, 
worked at a nearby road maintenance yard, Rivas said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
