<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
BRIEF FIRE ROUTS MIRAGE GUESTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Smoke from an electrical room fire triggered alarms at the luxury Mirage Hotel, 
prompting dozens of guests to evacuate. 
</P>
<P>
There were no injuries. 
</P>
<P>
Guests, many clad in pajamas, fled the second and third floors of the west wing 
of the 30-story hotel Thursday night as smoke drifted through hallways. The 
cause of the fire was under investigation. 
</P>
<P>
About 35 Clark County firefighters extinguished the blaze at 9:30 p.m., 45 
minutes after it began. The fire was confined by sprinklers to the power room 
on the mezzanine level, said hotel Chairman Steve Wynn. 
</P>
</TEXT>
