SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
ELV1S IS WORTH $132,000 IN UK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A British license plate spelling ELVIS fetched $132,000 at auction today. 
</P>
<P>
Businessman Anson Lane, 47, bought the plate ELV 1S for the price of a small 
London apartment even though he said he did not own a car to go with it. 
</P>
<P>
"I have a leased company car so now I will have to go out and buy a car of my 
own. A pink Cadillac would seem appropriate," he said. 
</P>
<P>
The status-conscious rich in Britain can pay the price of an average saloon car 
for the privilege of a personalized license plate, and the government has been 
cashing in by selling unique numbers that were previously withheld. 
</P>
<P>
License plates are made up of officially issued letters and figures. 
</P>
