<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
GABOR UNSURE HOW TO PLAY VEGAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actress Zsa Zsa Gabor has announced plans to play Las Vegas over the New Year's 
holiday, but she's unclear as to what she'll be doing. 
</P>
<P>
"Don't expect me to sing, don't expect me to do anything and then you'll be 
happy," she told a news conference Thursday. "Really, I'm too rich to work too 
hard." 
</P>
<P>
Gabor teamed with Vegas World Hotel owner Bob Stupak to announce her appearance 
at the resort's Galaxy Showroom Dec. 28-Jan. 2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
